\section*{Executive Summary}

The official PPG12 efficiency pipeline
(\texttt{RecoEffCalculator\_TTreeReader.C} $\to$ \texttt{MergeSim.C}
$\to$ \texttt{CalculatePhotonYield.C}) has been extended to produce
tower-index 2D acceptance maps at four selection levels (preselect,
common, tight, tight+iso) for both data and lumi-weighted inclusive MC
(signal + jet). All four maps are automatically written to
\texttt{Photon\_final\_\{var\_type\}.root} on every efficiency
production and are \etg-gated at $\ge 8$\,GeV (the cross-section
lower bin edge).

A full Phase-1 ($\to$ per-period DI-blended MC) + Phase-2 ($\to$
all-range merge + all-range data + \texttt{CalculatePhotonYield}) run
on \texttt{config\_bdt\_nom.yaml} produced the first apples-to-apples
comparison between data and inclusive MC. The principal findings:

\begin{enumerate}
  \item \crit{HIGH}\ --- \textbf{The MC simulation does not emulate
  all the dead towers active in data.} 108 towers in the fiducial
  $|\eta|<0.7$ region have zero data clusters at preselect while MC
  predicts a nonzero count; this grows to 244 towers at tight+iso.
  The severely-dead (z$<$-5) bin fraction of the data yield is
  \textbf{3.97\% at preselect}, \textbf{5.19\% at common},
  \textbf{25.05\% at tight}, and \textbf{53.58\% at tight+iso} — a
  monotonically growing bias consistent with shower leakage into dead
  towers progressively failing tighter selections.
  \item \crit{HIGH}\ --- \textbf{The cross-section is biased LOW}.
  \textbf{Direct measurement} via 9 symmetric-mask variants (see
  Section~\ref{sec:mask}) gave a shift $\sigma_{\rm mask}/\sigma_{\rm
  nom}$ ranging from +0.7\% (lightest mask) to +7.2\% (heaviest OR
  variant) \emph{under the initial per-bin Poisson z-score}. That
  approximation is not valid for the lumi-weight-combined MC; the
  report now uses an empirical R-distribution z-score
  (Section~\ref{sec:rstat}). Under the new method, many of the
  severity-tier mask variants collapse to the hard-dead mask, and the
  9-variant condor re-run with the updated masks is underway; numbers
  in Section~\ref{sec:mask} will be refreshed at that time.
  This effect is NOT currently captured by any systematic in the PPG12
  envelope.
  \item \warn{WARN}\ --- \textbf{At the tight/tight+iso levels, $\sim
  \,$14--44\% of bins have data excess (z$>$+2) over MC.} Bins with
  MC $N_{\rm eff} > 10$ show a genuine data excess; the top-5 such
  towers have data counts 44--70 vs MC expectation 1--4. These are
  candidate hot towers in data that should be cross-checked against
  sPHENIX run-by-run QA lists.
\end{enumerate}

\noindent\textbf{Overall}: the integration is correct (physics-review
PASS) and the numbers are independently re-derived
(numerical-rederivation PASS). The direct-measurement mask-variant
scan (9 variants $\times$ 3 families) gives shifts from
\textbf{+0.7\% (lightest single-level mask) to +7.2\% (heaviest OR
mask)}. We recommend \textbf{+7\% as the acceptance-mismodeling
systematic envelope}. The earlier tower-count-based $\sim$16\%
deficit was overstated because the bin-density metric inflates at the
tight-iso level where MC $N_{\rm eff}$ is low.

\medskip
\noindent\textbf{Nominal update (2026-04-22)}: the PPG12 nominal has
been switched from the 60cm-fiducial configuration (lumi
48.93\,pb$^{-1}$, \texttt{vertex\_cut\_truth=60}) to the all-z
configuration (beam-delivered lumi \textbf{64.37\,pb$^{-1}$},
\texttt{vertex\_cut\_truth=9999} widening the MBD-eff truth
denominator). The integrated cross-section under the new nominal in
\etg\,$\in [10, 36]$\,GeV is \textbf{$\sigma_{\rm nom} = 1963$\,pb}
($\approx 6\%$ lower than the retired 60cm value of 2091\,pb, driven
by the lumi change and the widened truth-vertex acceptance in the
MBD-eff denominator). All mask variants in this report are now
evaluated against the new nominal.

\medskip
\noindent\textbf{Scope}: results here are for the new allz nominal and
its 9 mask variants only. The tower-map histograms are populated
automatically for every variant, so future scans are trivial.

