\subsection{Methodology}

For each $(i\eta, i\phi)$ bin we have $n_{\rm MC}[i,j]$ (weighted
count) and $n_{\rm data}[i,j]$ (raw count). The MC
effective-$N$ per bin is
$N_{\rm eff}[i,j] = n_{\rm MC}^2/\sigma^2_{\rm MC}$ where
$\sigma^2_{\rm MC}$ is the stored sumw2. Define densities
$p_{\rm MC}=n_{\rm MC}/N_{\rm MC}$ and
$p_{\rm data}=n_{\rm data}/N_{\rm data}$ (globals). The per-bin
ratio $R=p_{\rm data}/p_{\rm MC}$ has the Poisson relative
uncertainty
\[
  \sigma_R/R = \sqrt{1/\max(n_{\rm data}, 1) + 1/N_{\rm eff}}\,,\qquad
  z = (R-1)/(R\cdot\sigma_R/R)\,.
\]

The \emph{deficit} attributable to dead-in-data regions is computed as
\[
  {\rm deficit} = \sum_{z<\text{thr}} \max(0,\, \mu - n_{\rm data})
  \quad\text{with}\quad
  \mu = n_{\rm MC}\cdot N_{\rm data}/N_{\rm MC}\,.
\]
Hard-dead bins ($n_{\rm data}=0$, $n_{\rm MC}>0$) have
$z\to-\infty$ and contribute $\mu$ to the deficit sum. The fiducial
restriction is $i\eta \in [17, 78]$, equivalent to $|\eta|<0.7$ at the
tower-center resolution.

\section{Results per Selection Level}

The full-range and fiducial ($|\eta|<0.7$) quantitative summary is in
Tables~\ref{tab:summary_full} and~\ref{tab:summary_fid}. Figures
\ref{fig:preselect}--\ref{fig:tight_iso} show, for each level, the 2D
tower maps of: (top-left) inclusive MC, (top-right) data,
(bottom-left) normalized ratio, (bottom-right) Poisson z-score.

\begin{table}[H]
  \centering
  \caption{Full-range ($i\eta \in [0,95]$) data/inclusive-MC tower
  comparison summary. $N_{\rm eff}^{\rm med}$ is the median MC
  effective $N$ per filled bin.
  "Hard-dead" means bins where MC predicts clusters but data has zero.
  Percentages in \%-Bins columns are fractions of bins with finite
  z-score (bulk: 24576 total, minus hard-dead, minus both-empty).
  "def" is the aggregated $\max(0,\mu-n_{\rm data})$ in units of
  $N_{\rm data}$; "exc" is the aggregated $\max(0,n_{\rm data}-\mu)$
