\section{Tower Category Maps}

Figure~\ref{fig:category} shows, for each selection level, a single
2D tower map with four discrete categories:
\begin{itemize}
  \item \textbf{Dark red (hard dead)}: $n_{\rm data}=0$ in a bin
  where inclusive MC predicts nonzero yield. These are the towers
  directly responsible for the A-region bias and are the natural
  targets for the MC mask fix.
  \item \textbf{Orange} ($z<-5$, $n_{\rm data}>0$): severe data
  suppression relative to MC but not fully dead --- consistent with
  partially-functional towers or shower leakage into adjacent dead
  towers.
  \item \textbf{Yellow} ($-5 < z < -2$): moderate data deficit.
  Bulk of this set is dominated by the shower-leakage halo around
  actual dead towers.
  \item \textbf{Light gray}: $|z|\le 2$ or MC empty. Bulk of the
  fiducial is in this category (data/MC agree within Poisson).
\end{itemize}
The blue dashed rectangle marks the analysis fiducial
$i\eta\in[17,78]$ ($|\eta|<0.7$). Outside this region both samples
are suppressed by the common NPB cut (NPB is not scored for
$|\eta|\geq 0.7$), which explains the red border at tight and
tight+iso.

