\subsection{Absolute cross-section spectrum}
\label{sec:mask_spectrum}

Figure~\ref{fig:mask_spectrum} shows
$d\sigma/d\etg$ for the nominal and all 9 variants. At visual
log-scale the shifts are essentially invisible (as expected for
$\lesssim 7\%$ effects) --- the shape of the spectrum is preserved
across all masks. No variant produces a catastrophic pT-dependent
distortion; the shifts are smooth and distribute across bins.

\begin{figure}[H]
  \centering
  \includegraphics[width=0.66\textwidth]{\figdir/mask_variant_xsec_spectrum.pdf}
  \caption{Differential cross-section $d\sigma/d\etg$ in $|\eta|<0.7$
  for the nominal allz configuration (open circles) and the 9 mask
  variants, grouped by family (common, tight, OR). Spectrum shape is
  preserved across all variants; the few-percent shifts are too small
  to see on log-y axis. Use Fig.~\ref{fig:mask_bybin} for the per-bin
  ratio view.}
  \label{fig:mask_spectrum}
\end{figure}

