\begin{figure}[H]
  \centering
  \includegraphics[width=0.78\textwidth]{\figdir/mask_variant_bybin.pdf}
  \caption{Per-bin $\sigma_{\rm masked} / \sigma_{\rm nominal}$ vs
  $\etg$ in three panels: \textbf{top} = common-level mask family,
  \textbf{middle} = tight-level family, \textbf{bottom} = OR family
  (union of common + tight at each severity). Hard-dead-only
  (circles) is smooth and monotonically rising from +0.6--1.3\% at
  low $\etg$ to +1.2--1.6\% at 32-36\,GeV. Heavier masks
  ($+\,z<-5$, $+\,z<-2$) show wider scatter above $\etg\sim 22$ GeV
  where per-bin MC $N_{\rm eff}$ drops. Dashed gray = nominal
  reference.}
  \label{fig:mask_bybin}
\end{figure}

\subsection{Interpretation}

\textbf{Shifts are all positive and much smaller than the tower-count
estimate (16\%) predicted.} Three observations:

\begin{enumerate}
  \item \textbf{Sign is consistent with the hypothesis.} Symmetric
  masking removes MC content in data-dead regions. Since data had zero
  there to begin with, the MC-only contribution was inflating
  $\varepsilon_{\rm MC}$ and suppressing the measured cross-section.
  Removing the asymmetry raises $\sigma$.
  \item \textbf{Tower-count overestimates the bias.} The tight-level
  z$<$-2 tower deficit was 63.99\% of the data yield (Table~2) while
  the cross-section shift under the same mask is only +4.87\%,
  and the largest OR-family shift is +7.17\%. The ratio tower-deficit
  to $\sigma$-shift is 10--15 --- because (a) the tower deficit is evaluated
  at the tight-iso density level where MC $N_{\rm eff}$ is low and
  stat fluctuations dominate the one-sided tail, (b) unfolding smears
  narrow features back into neighbor pT bins, and (c) the efficiency
  correction partly absorbs the MC-side deficit as well.
  \item \textbf{Severity progression is nearly linear and hasn't
  plateaued.} If the analysis were fully recovering the bias, the
  severity-3 point would plateau; instead it's still climbing (4.5\%
  $\to$ 4.9\%). This means even the heaviest mask underestimates the
  true physical dead-tower coverage, and the real bias might be a few
  \% larger than our envelope.
\end{enumerate}

\subsection{Official cross-section plots (data vs NLO theory)}
\label{sec:mask_official}

For visual comparison of the mask variants against the theory
reference (JETPHOX NLO with CT14/BFG~II, and NLO pQCD by
W.~Vogelsang), we regenerated the standard PPG12 final-cross-section
plot (\texttt{plot\_final\_selection.C}) for the new allz nominal
and all 9 mask variants. Each plot shows
$d^2\sigma/d\eta\,d\etg$ vs $\etg$ with Data (blue circles) overlaid
on theory predictions, plus the Theory/Data ratio in the lower panel.
Figure~\ref{fig:mask_official} shows the nominal alongside the
three heaviest family variants --- the subtle upward shift in data
(toward the theory curves) under masking is visible in the ratio
panel.

