  the GitHub Pages site.}
  \label{fig:mask_official}
\end{figure}

\subsection{Recommended envelope}

With the OR family now providing a more-conservative mask (union of
common + tight at each severity), the heaviest variant
\texttt{mask\_or\_harddead\_zlt2} gives
$\sigma_{\rm masked} / \sigma_{\rm nom} = 1.072$, i.e.\
\textbf{+7.2\% one-sided on the cross-section}. This is the
recommended acceptance-mask systematic envelope. The
tower-count-based ``$\sim$16\%'' earlier in this report is a bin-density
proxy and should be treated as informational only; the direct
measurement supersedes it.

\medskip
If the MC dead-tower list is eventually fixed at the simulation
stage, rerun the 9 variants --- the shifts should drop toward zero,
and the remaining residuals define the post-fix systematic.

\section{Recommendations}

\begin{enumerate}
  \item \textbf{Fix the MC dead-tower list (HIGH-1, HIGH-2).}
  Candidate locations to investigate for Run-24 data:
  \texttt{CaloTowerStatus} (sPHENIX CDB dead/hot-tower entries), the
  anatree step's tower-calibrator / retower module, and any explicit
  hot-tower list passed to \texttt{CaloAna24.cc}. Apply the same
  masking at the MC side --- either at the GEANT/digitization stage or
  as a post-hoc mask in the slimtree writer. Re-run the nominal
  pipeline and re-check Tables~\ref{tab:summary_full}
  and~\ref{tab:summary_fid}; the net-tight deficit should drop to
  $\mathcal{O}$(1\%) once MC masking matches data.
  \item \textbf{Cross-check the top data-excess towers (WARN-1).}
  Query sPHENIX run-by-run hot-tower QA for the 5 towers in
  Table~\ref{tab:hot_tight_iso}. If confirmed hot in data, add to the
  analysis-side tower mask (applied to both data and MC) rather than
  just to MC.
  \item \textbf{Interim systematic placeholder.} Pending the fix,
  assign a \textbf{+7\% acceptance-mismatch systematic} on the
  cross-section (one-sided, based on the heaviest mask variant
  \texttt{mask\_or\_harddead\_zlt2} which gives +7.17\%; see
  Section~\ref{sec:mask}). Add this to \texttt{calc\_syst\_bdt.py}
  as a new \texttt{acceptance} group. This number supersedes the
  tower-count-based $\sim$16--20\% estimate and reflects the direct,
  symmetric-mask measurement.
  \item \textbf{Improve MC statistics at tight level.} The median
  $N_{\rm eff}=3.8$ at tight is a statistical limit even after
  inclusive-MC hadd. Consider either (a) aggregating bins into
  $4\times 4$ tower groups for the diagnostic, or (b) running
  additional jet MC mass production to raise per-bin stats.
  \item \textbf{Wire into the standard plotting pipeline.} Add a
  one-line call to run \texttt{quantify\_tower\_mismatch\_official.C}
  at the end of every efficiency production so every cross-section
  variant ships with its own acceptance-mismatch diagnostic.
\end{enumerate}

